quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  33,63,"People ask you regarding the Last Day; proclaim, “Its knowledge is only with Allah; and what do you know, the Last Day may really be near!”"
  33,64,"Allah has indeed cursed the disbelievers, and has kept prepared for them a blazing fire."
  33,65,"In which they will remain forever; in it they will find neither a protector nor any supporter."
  33,66,"On the day when their faces will be overturned being roasted inside the fire, they will say, “Alas – if only we had obeyed Allah and obeyed His Noble Messenger!”"
  33,67,"And they will say, “Our Lord! We followed our chiefs and our elders – so they misled us from the path!”"
  33,68,"“Our Lord! Give them double the punishment of the fire and send upon them a mighty curse!”"
  33,69,"O People who Believe! Do not be like the people who troubled Moosa – so Allah freed him from the allegations they had uttered; and Moosa is honourable in the sight of Allah."
  33,70,"O People who Believe! Fear Allah, and speak rightly."
  33,71,"He will rectify your deeds for you and forgive you your sins; and whoever obeys Allah and His Noble Messenger, has indeed achieved a great success."
  33,72,"We indeed offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they refused it and were afraid of it – and man accepted it; indeed he is one who puts himself into hardship, is extremely unwise."
  33,73,"In order that Allah may punish the hypocrite men, and the hypocrite women, and the polytheist men, and the polytheist women – and accept the repentance of believing men and believing women; and Allah is Oft Forgiving, Most Merciful."
